# Signed Plugin Release Flow

When the user provides a signed plugin zip path (TPC/TAK Signed), perform this flow end-to-end:

1. Verify `main` is current and pushed (`git status`, `git log -1`, `git push origin main`).
2. Inspect the zip and extract the signed APK.
3. Validate APK package/version metadata before deploy.
4. Create/push release tag `v<version>` on the release commit if missing, then create/update GitHub Release and attach signed APK/AAB and source submission zip.
5. Upload APK to cloud plugin path (`/var/www/html/plugins/com.uvpro.plugin.apk`).
6. Update server `generate_infz.py` version + version_code to match the signed APK.
7. Regenerate `product.infz` and sync to `/var/www/html/plugins/5.5.1/product.infz`.
8. Verify:
   - `product.inf` row version/version_code/hash/size matches the signed APK
   - canonical and versioned APK URLs return HTTP 200
9. Report final deployed version, release tag URL, hash, and URLs to the user.

Prefer explicit verification over assumptions. If any step fails, stop and report the exact blocker.
